from keras.models import Sequential
from keras.layers import Dense, Activation, Dropout
from keras.callbacks import EarlyStopping
from pyspark.sql.functions import udf
from pyspark.sql.types import DoubleType
from pyjake.sparkmodule import udf_dt2d, udf_dt2t, udf_delsec
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from matplotlib import pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

sns.set()

udf_il_scaler = udf(lambda v: v / 100000, DoubleType())
udf_sz_scaler = udf(lambda v: v / 100, DoubleType())

udf_log = udf(lambda v: np.log(v), DoubleType())
udf_scaler_doy = udf(lambda i: i/366, DoubleType())

casa = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///nl/witlab/cas/casa.parquet')
time = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///sun/srs_min.parquet')

spdf = casa.join(time, ['date', 'time'])\
           .select('date', 'time', 'illum', 'uvi', 'solar_zenith', 'day_of_year')\
           .withColumn('illum_s', udf_il_scaler('illum'))\
           .withColumn('sz_s', udf_sz_scaler('solar_zenith'))\
           .withColumn('doy_s', udf_scaler_doy('day_of_year'))

paragraphs.title: init dataset
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

# x_feature_cols = ['illum_s', 'sz_s', 'relative', 'doy_s']
# x_feature_cols = ['illum_s', 'sz_s', 'cct_s']

x_feature_cols = ['illum_s', 'sz_s', 'doy_s']
y_label_cols = 'uvi'

spdf_train_b, spdf_test = spdf.randomSplit([0.8, 0.2], 7)
spdf_train, spdf_val = spdf_train_b.randomSplit([0.8, 0.2], 7)

pdf = spdf.toPandas()
pdf_train = spdf_train.toPandas()
pdf_test = spdf_test.toPandas()
pdf_val = spdf_val.toPandas()

x_train = np.array(pdf_train[x_feature_cols])
y_train = np.array(pdf_train[y_label_cols])

x_val = np.array(pdf_val[x_feature_cols])
y_val = np.array(pdf_val[y_label_cols])

x_test = np.array(pdf_test[x_feature_cols])
y_test = np.array(pdf_test[y_label_cols])

print('x train len:', len(x_train))
print('y train len:', len(y_train))
print('x val len:', len(x_val))
print('y val len:', len(y_val))
print('x test len:', len(x_test))
print('y test len:', len(y_test))

# Random Forest

%pyspark

from pyspark.mllib.regression import LabeledPoint
from pyspark.mllib.tree import RandomForest, RandomForestModel
from pyspark.mllib.util import MLUtils

# Load and parse the data file into an RDD of LabeledPoint.
trainingData = spdf_train.select('illum', 'solar_zenith', 'day_of_year', 'uvi')\
                         .rdd.map(lambda r: LabeledPoint(r['uvi'], [r['illum'], r['solar_zenith'], r['day_of_year']]))

testData = spdf_test.select('illum', 'solar_zenith', 'day_of_year', 'uvi')\
                    .rdd.map(lambda r: LabeledPoint(r['uvi'], [r['illum'], r['solar_zenith'], r['day_of_year']]))

model = RandomForest.trainRegressor(trainingData, categoricalFeaturesInfo={},
                                    featureSubsetStrategy="auto", impurity='variance', 
                                    numTrees=20, maxDepth=30, maxBins=128)

# Evaluate model on test instances and compute test error
predictions = model.predict(testData.map(lambda x: x.features))
labelsAndPredictions = testData.map(lambda lp: lp.label).zip(predictions)

print(predictions.collect()[:5])

# testMAE = labelsAndPredictions.map(lambda lp: np.abs(lp[0] - lp[1]))\
#                               .sum() / float(testData.count())
# testMSE = labelsAndPredictions.map(lambda lp: (lp[0] - lp[1]) ** 2)\
#                               .sum() / float(testData.count())
testMAPE = labelsAndPredictions.map(lambda lp: np.abs((lp[0] - lp[1]) / lp[0]))\
                              .sum() * 100 / float(testData.count())

print('mape:', testMAPE)

%pyspark

import numpy as np
from sklearn.svm import SVR
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# #############################################################################
# Generate sample data
X = np.sort(5 * np.random.rand(40, 1), axis=0)
y = np.sin(X).ravel()

# #############################################################################
# Add noise to targets
y[::5] += 3 * (0.5 - np.random.rand(8))

# #############################################################################
# Fit regression model
svr_rbf = SVR(kernel='rbf', C=100, gamma=0.1, epsilon=.1)
svr_lin = SVR(kernel='linear', C=100, gamma='auto')
svr_poly = SVR(kernel='poly', C=100, gamma='auto', degree=3, epsilon=.1,
               coef0=1)

# #############################################################################
# Look at the results
lw = 2

# svrs = [svr_rbf, svr_lin, svr_poly]
# kernel_label = ['RBF', 'Linear', 'Polynomial']
# model_color = ['m', 'c', 'g']

svrs = [svr_poly]
kernel_label = ['Polynomial']
model_color = ['g']

fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=1, ncols=2, figsize=(15, 10), sharey=True)
for ix, svr in enumerate(svrs):
    axes[ix].plot(X, svr.fit(X, y).predict(X), color=model_color[ix], lw=lw,
                  label='{} model'.format(kernel_label[ix]))
    axes[ix].scatter(X[svr.support_], y[svr.support_], facecolor="none",
                     edgecolor=model_color[ix], s=50,
                     label='{} support vectors'.format(kernel_label[ix]))
    axes[ix].scatter(X[np.setdiff1d(np.arange(len(X)), svr.support_)],
                     y[np.setdiff1d(np.arange(len(X)), svr.support_)],
                     facecolor="none", edgecolor="k", s=50,
                     label='other training data')
    axes[ix].legend(loc='upper center', bbox_to_anchor=(0.5, 1.1),
                    ncol=1, fancybox=True, shadow=True)

fig.text(0.5, 0.04, 'data', ha='center', va='center')
fig.text(0.06, 0.5, 'target', ha='center', va='center', rotation='vertical')
fig.suptitle("Support Vector Regression", fontsize=14)
plt.show()
